@tqchen ,
I think the three third-party libraries (binary version) are not difficult to install. The links are all their official sites. The only works for users to do are downloading and installing / extacting them.

Sorry for delayed reply. Seems we have not yet support using numpy in validation. This however, should be readily supported by taking a tuple of data, label as you suggested. 

We can easily convert the data, label tuple into a DataIter wanted by this funciton https://github.com/dmlc/mxnet/blob/master/python/mxnet/model.py#L648

